# Proxmox — Agents Execute Everything (Critical)

## CRITICAL

**Never ask Morgan to open the Proxmox UI, SSH to the hypervisor, paste cron lines, or “run this on PVE”.** You have the same credentials as other automation: `.credentials.local` (`PROXMOX_TOKEN_ID`, `PROXMOX_TOKEN_SECRET`, `PROXMOX_HOST` / `PROXMOX_HOSTS`, `PROXMOX202_PASSWORD` / `VM_PASSWORD` for root SSH to the PVE host when API tokens are insufficient). Use **`python scripts/proxmox/apply_production_vm_policy_api.py`** after loading credentials.

## Required behavior

| Task | Agent action |
|------|----------------|
| Set **Start at boot**, start stopped production VMs | Run `apply_production_vm_policy_api.py` (uses API + optional SSH side effects) |
| Daily backup / vzdump / ensure-running cron on PVE | Same script (`--api-only` skips SSH install only when SSH is genuinely unavailable) |
| List VMs / diagnose | Proxmox API via token or `infrastructure-ops` + MCP `ssh_exec` to **root@PVE** when API fails |
| Token missing | Add placeholder keys to `.credentials.local` template only — never commit secrets; rotate any token that appeared in old scripts |

## Failure handling

If the dev PC cannot reach `192.168.0.x`, report **network reachability** with evidence (timeout, unreachable). Do not ask Morgan to click Proxmox; retry from a context that has LAN access or fix routing. Still **attempt** API/SSH once per session when policy work is requested.

